    "finalTextLength": 3003,
    "finalText": "Start with the biggest hole: you don’t have a reliable single source of truth for who owns what, what’s due, and what’s blocked. The systems and processes below directly address that, based on where evidence is thinnest and risk is highest.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Centralized Work Tracker\n\nYou need a live tracking system — not spreadsheets, not email chains. One place where every commitment (operations, accounting, marketing, field) is logged with:\n- **Clear owner**\n- **Due date**\n- **Status/Blocker**\n- **Last review date**\n\nNothing gets “talked about” twice — it’s logged, owned, and closed or escalated. No duplicate outreach. No lost issues.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Weekly Intake & Review Cadence\n\nFormalize a **weekly operating schedule** for critical workflows:\n- **Mail processing & document collection:** All incoming paperwork (AP, AR, tax, contracts) scanned, coded, and logged. Exception buckets flagged for review.\n- **Team work review:** Every item in the centralized tracker is reviewed weekly. Single owner per issue — no group “we’ll follow up”.\n- **Accounting/Back-office check:** Thursdays for regular, Fridays for overflow. Confirmed by whoever owns accounting admin (Shania, Maria, Misty, as mentioned).\n\n---\n\n## 3. Defined Escalation and Exception Handling\n\n- If something’s at risk or blocked, it moves from “owner” to escalation mode in the tracker: flagged, with the next step/time.\n- Meeting outcomes and action items go into the same system — not left in transcripts or emails.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Document Control\n\nYou’re handling design milestone schedules and invoices, but evidence shows versioning and approval steps are informal. You need:\n- **Version history** on all milestone documents, drawings, and invoices.\n- A documented approval checklist, especially for pay app and milestone release.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Monthly Marketing & Reporting Packs\n\nStandardize marketing and operations reporting:\n- Fixed template\n- Named metrics (reach, interaction, conversion, spend)\n- Due date\n- Locked submission process (no last-minute chasing)\n\n---\n\n## 6. Simple Operational Dashboard\n\nLeverage the centralized tracker for a **live dashboard**:\n- Overdue items\n- Upcoming commitments\n- Open exceptions (missing docs, billing delays, audit flags)\n- Financial status (aging, margin/cost overrun)\n\n---\n\n## 7. Portfolio-wide Risk Visibility\n\nWithout reliable data, leadership is blind to systemic risk. Once above is handled:\n- Use the dashboard to summarize risk across all active projects.\n- Drill down to blockers, financial issues, team constraints fast — not by combing through emails.\n\n---\n\n### Bottom Line\n\nUntil you have a disciplined, recurring operating cadence for intake, ownership, follow-up, and escalation, you’re always going to be fighting fires by email. Build that backbone now. If you want direct tool recs, I can spec options and priorities — but the above is the non-negotiable foundation.\n\nReady for the tactical version? Or do you want suggestions on software/platforms to fit these processes?"
  },
